  "text": "Tissue preparation. At 3 wk after elastase injection, the hamsters were euthanized, and the lungs and femurs were removed. A saline-displacement technique was used to measure excised lung volume at 0 cmH2O airway pressure [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The right femurs were wrapped in saline-soaked gauze and placed in a Ϫ20°F freezer for subsequent densitometry and mechanical testing. The left femurs were fixed in 10% neutral buffered formalin and used for structural and dynamic histomorphometric measurements.",
